5 Ingredient Oreo Cake Doughnuts. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Crush about 20 Oreos in a food processor
- In the bowl of a stand mixer, combine 2 cups of self rising flour with 1 cup of crushed Oreos and 1 cup of greek yogurt
- When the dough pulls together, turn it out on a floured surface for a few minutes just until the dough is smooth
- Roll out the dough until its about 2 inches thick, and then use a large cookie cutter to make teh doughnut shape, and a smaller cookie cutter to cut out the inside
- reserve the small insides for doughnut ho9les
- Place the doughnuts on a parchment paper lined baking tray and let rest for 5 minutes
- Bake the doughnuts at 400 degrees F for 10 minutes, flipping halfway through
- In the meantime, combine 2 cups of powdered sugar with 1/4 cup of corn syrup
- Dip the cooled doughnuts in the glaze letting any excess glaze drip off and then place them on a wire rack
- Garnish with some additional crushed Oreos

Buffalo Chicken Jalapeño Popper Bites. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Season 1/2 pound of chicken breasts with salt and onion powder
- Fry them on medium high for 3 minutes a side and transfer the chicken toa food processor
- Pulse the chicken a few times to break it up, then add 1/2 cup of cooked bacon bits, 1 cup of room temperature cream cheese, 1 cup of sharp shredded cheddar, 1 tablespoon of onion powder, garlic powder, and paprika, and a pinch of salt.
- Run the food processor and then add 1/4 cup of your favorite hot sauce
- Transfer the mixture to a piping bag or p[lastic freezer bag
- Cut the top off a large jalapeño and using a fork, scoop out the seeds and stems from the inside
- Fill the jalapeno up with the chicken and cheese mixture and then slice them into 1 inch pieces
- Put them in the freezer for about 10 minutes
- In a bowl combine 5 eggs with 1/2 cup of hot sauce and in another bowl combine 2 cups of all purpose flour with 1/4 cup of paprika and garlic powder and ina 3rd bowl 2 cups of bread crumbs
- Coat the jalapeño piece in the flour, the in the egg wash, then in the bread crumbs, then back in the egg wash and breadcrumbs for a double dredge
- Fry the jalapeños at 375 degrees F for 3-4 minutes or airfryer at 425 for 10 minutes

Big Mac Inspired Hot Dog aka a McGlizzy. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Start off by making the sesame seed buns but using top cut (New England) buns
- Coat the with a beaten egg wash and then sprinkle on some sesame seeds
- Bake the buns at 450 degrees F for 5 minutes
- For the big mac sauce, combine 1/2 cup of mayonnaise, 1/4 cup of ketchup and mustard, 1 tablespoon of garlic and onion powder, 1 tablespoon of sweet relish and white vinegar, and season with salt and pepper
- Fry a few all beef hot dogs to your liking and set them aside
- Assemble the hot dogs by adding some sauce on the inside followed by a bit of small diced onions
- On top of the onions add some shredded iceberg lettuce followed by a couple slices of American cheese
- Add a few slices of mini dill pickles between the bun and the cheese. The cheese will help the pickles stay in place
- Add the hot dog on top of the cheese followed by some more diced onions and some more Big Mac sauce

The easiest and most delicious Sweet Chili Wings made with @ninjakitchen Ninja Foodi XL Pressure Cooker. I love the SteamCrisp function where you can steam and crisp at the same time giving you a crispy outside but juicy inside.  Follow the recipe 👇🏻
 #SponsoredbyNinja #NinjaFoodiPressureCooker #NinjaFoodiFamily
·   Pat about 3 pounds of chicken wings dry.
·   Toss the chicken wings in 1 tablespoon of salt and 1 tablespoon of baking powder.
·   To the bowl of the Nina Foodi, add 1 cup of chicken stock and place the crisping basket inside.
·   Add the chicken wings to the crisping basket. Slice the Ninja Foodi to the Steam Crisp option. Cook at 450 degrees for 20 minutes.
·   Take the wings out and set them aside.
·   Take the crisping basket out and flip the Ninja Foodi to sear and saute.
·   Add 1/4 cup of rice vinegar, 1/4 cup of water, 1/4 cup of white sugar, 1 tablespoon of sambal oelek chili sauce, 2 cloves of minced garlic, 1 tablespoon of minced ginger, 1 tablespoon of soy sauce and bring to a simmer.
·   While it simmers, combine 2 teaspoons of cornstarch with 2 teaspoons of water.
·   Add the cornstarch slurry to the pot and mix until it thickens.
·   Add the wings back in the pot and toss with the sauce.
·   Garnish with chopped green onions and enjoy!

How to Slice and DIce and Avocado. Follow these steps👇🏻
- Cut an avocado in half along the seed
- Separate the two sides of the avocado
- For the diced version, slice the inside part of the avocado lengthwise, and then cut it perpendicular to create the dice
- Use a spoon to scoop out the flesh
- For the slices, do the exact same thing except don't cut it the second time
- Scoop out the inside like you would for the diced avocado!
